From Robert Abbott Subject Re water in trunk of Probe In article r crn , Tommy Szeto writes Water gradually builds up in the trunk of my friend's Ford Probe Every once in a while we would have to remove the spare and scoop out the water under the plywood carpet cover on the trunk I would guess this usually happens after a good thunder storm A few Qs Is this a common problem Where are the drain holes located for the hatch I had the same problem in my ' MX Luckily I had it fixed under warranty I think they replaced a tail light gasket Check with a dealer, it's a known problem Robert K Abbott